<!-- This article was automatically created by [[User:polbot]] from http://bioguide.congress.gov/scripts/biodisplay.pl?index=B000298. The prose may be stilted, and there may be grammatical and Wikification errors. Please improve in any way you see fit. -->'''Berkley Warren Bedell''' (born [[March 5]], [[1921]]) is a [[United States House of Representatives|U.S. Representative]] from [[Iowa]].

Born in [[Spirit Lake, Iowa]], Bedell was educated in Spirit Lake public schools.
He graduated from Spirit Lake High School, 1939.
He attended [[Iowa State University]], Ames from 1940 to 1942.
He engaged in fishing tackle business.
<!-- A grammar fix may be needed here. -->Founder and chairman of Berkley &amp.
<!-- A grammar fix may be needed here. -->Co., Spirit Lake.
He served in [[United States Army]], first lieutenant from 1942 to 1945.
He served as member of the Spirit Lake Board of Education from 1957 to 1962.
He was an unsuccessful candidate for election in 1972 to the Ninety-third Congress.
He served as delegate to Iowa State Democratic conventions from 1972 to 1974.

Bedell was elected as a [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democrat]] to the Ninety-fourth and to the five succeeding Congresses ([[January 3]], [[1975]]-[[January 3]], [[1987]]).
He was not a candidate for reelection in 1986.
He is a resident of [[Spirit Lake, Iowa]].

